<abstract>
<p>Rǝtuʿa Hāymānot is a collection of homilies focusing on the events of the Passion cycle. Most probably it is an indigenous
  Ethiopian production. Its as author must have lived ca. 1375 and there is some ground to identify him
  with <persName ref="PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName>. It should not be confused with a collection of homilies
preserved in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1763">EMML 1763</ref>, <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML8509">EMML 8509</ref>
and <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient8192">BL Or. 8192</ref>, with which however it shows some textual affinities.</p>
</abstract>
